# Install apache2-utils if needed: apt install apache2-utils
echo $(htpasswd -nB admin) | sed -e 's/\$/\$\$/g'
That outputs something like admin:$$2y$$05$$... — paste that as:


NETDATA_AUTH=admin:$$2y$$05$$...
Summary of what was added:

docker-compose.prod.yml:

Netdata service with pid: host + required capabilities so it can see host processes and containers
Traefik labels route https://m.santoshdevops.cloud → port 19999 with auto TLS
Basic auth middleware (NETDATA_AUTH env var) protects the dashboard
150M RAM / 0.25 CPU limits — fits within the 2GB server budget
Two named volumes (netdata-lib, netdata-cache) for persistent metrics
netdata/netdata.conf:

update every = 2 — polls every 2s instead of 1s (halves CPU)
process scheduling policy = idle — lowest OS priority, never starves your app
dbengine with 1 day retention + 32MB page cache
ML/anomaly detection disabled (saves ~20MB RAM + CPU)
Heavy plugins disabled: apps, fping, ioping, perf, nfacct
proc + cgroups + diskspace kept on — these give you CPU, RAM, network, disk, and per-container metrics